Version 2: Using Interfaces
Question:
Enhance the BankAccount system to include account services and operations. Follow these instructions:

Create a class BankAccount with the following:

Attributes:
String accountNumber
String accountHolder
double balance
Methods:
void deposit(double amount)
void withdraw(double amount)
Create an interface AccountOperations with methods:

void displayAccountDetails(): Displays account details.
void calculateAnnualInterest(): Calculates and displays the annual interest (applies only to SavingsAccount).
Create subclasses:

SavingsAccount: Implements AccountOperations. Add an attribute double interestRate.
CurrentAccount: Implements AccountOperations. Add an attribute double overdraftLimit.
Allow users to:

Create either a Savings or Current account.
Perform deposit/withdrawal operations.
Display account details and calculate annual interest if applicable.

Choose Account Type:
1. Savings Account
2. Current Account
